                    <h2>Understanding Deepfakes</h2>
                    
                    <p>
                        Deepfakes are synthetic media created using artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques 
                        to replace the likeness of one person with that of another in video or audio. The term "deepfake" 
                        combines "deep learning" and "fake," reflecting the technology used to create them.
                    </p>

                    <div class="info-box">
                        <h3>📌 Key Definition</h3>
                        <p>
                            A deepfake is a piece of media that has been synthetically created or manipulated using deep learning 
                            techniques, typically a convolutional neural network, to convincingly replace a person with a digital 
                            replica in video or audio content.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <h3>How Deepfakes Are Created</h3>
                    <p>
                        The creation of deepfakes involves several key steps:
                    </p>

                    <ol>
                        <li><strong>Data Collection:</strong> Large datasets of images or videos of the target person are gathered.</li>
                        <li><strong>Face Detection:</strong> The system identifies and isolates faces from the collected media.</li>
                        <li><strong>Feature Extraction:</strong> Neural networks analyze facial features and expressions.</li>
                        <li><strong>Training:</strong> A generative model (often a GAN - Generative Adversarial Network) is trained to learn the mapping between faces.</li>
                        <li><strong>Generation:</strong> The trained model creates realistic facial representations in new videos.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <h3>Common Applications</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Entertainment and film production</li>
                        <li>Educational content creation</li>
                        <li>Video game character animation</li>
                        <li>Accessibility - creating sign language interpretations</li>
                        <li>Medical training and simulations</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="warning-box">
                        <h3>⚠️ Misuse Concerns</h3>
                        <p>
                            Despite legitimate uses, deepfakes have raised significant concerns about:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Non-consensual intimate media</li>
                            <li>Political manipulation and misinformation</li>
                            <li>Fraud and identity theft</li>
                            <li>Defamation and harassment</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <h3>Why Detection Matters</h3>
                    <p>
                        As deepfake technology becomes more sophisticated, the ability to detect manipulated media becomes 
                        increasingly important. In this course, we'll learn various techniques to identify deepfakes and 
                        understand the tools and methods used to create them. This knowledge is crucial for:
                    </p>

                    <ul>
                        <li>Protecting against misinformation</li>
                        <li>Verifying the authenticity of media</li>
                        <li>Understanding AI capabilities and limitations</li>
                        <li>Making informed decisions about digital content</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="key-takeaways">
                        <h3>✓ Key Takeaways</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Deepfakes are AI-generated synthetic media that can convincingly replace people in videos or audio</li>
                            <li>They are created using deep learning techniques, particularly GANs</li>
                            <li>While they have legitimate uses, they pose significant risks when misused</li>
                            <li>Detection and verification of authentic media are becoming increasingly important</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </section>

